      "id": "0afa3758-6510-4cc0-871e-997c658321e6",
      "name": "Sticky Note"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## What does it do?\n**Objective:** Automatically fetch reels from creators, generate insights using Gemini AI, and update Airtable with video guidelines \u2014 fully automated and repeatable.\n\n**Why important?:**\n- Stop wasting time guessing what to post.\n- Steal proven ideas that are already working.\n- Save hours on research every week.\n---\n\nIf you create content, work with clients, or run a personal brand\u2014this system will give you a creative edge.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 320,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "0f62731b-5b03-450c-a009-04ab1c5648f0",
      "name": "Sticky Note1",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -672,
        1184
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Contact us\nHave questions, found a bug, or have ideas to improve this workflow?\nWe're here to help and always open to feedback!\n\n\ud83d\udca1 Suggest an improvement \u2014 Got a cool idea to make this workflow better? Let us know!\n\n\ud83d\udc1e Found a bug? \u2014 Tell us what went wrong so we can fix it fast.\n\n\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Need help? \u2014 Whether you're stuck or unsure how to use a part of the workflow, just reach out.\n\n\ud83d\udce9 Contact: charlie@jobescape.me\n\nWe typically respond within 72 hours on business days.\n\n",
        "height": 452,
        "width": 320
      },
      "id": "ea3e29cc-0a8c-403c-92d9-04d56bd500b8",
      "name": "Sticky Note7",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -672,
        1840
      ],
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Instructions\n## 1. Airtable Settings\n### Step 1: Copy the Airtable Database\n- Go to https://airtable.com/YOUR_AIRTABLE_BASE_ID/YOUR_AIRTABLE_SHARE_ID\n- Click \"Copy Base\" in the top-left corner\n- Create or log into your Airtable account\n\n### Step 2: Create Airtable Access Token\n- Go to https://airtable.com/create/tokens\n- Generate Token\n- Grant necessary permissions\n- Paste this token into the Airtable node in your n8n workflow\n\n### Step 3: Add Influencer Handles to Airtable\n- Open your copied Airtable base\n- Go to creators section\n- Add the influencers you want to analyze in the relevant column\n\n\n---\n\n## 2. Apify Settings\n### Step 1: Create an Apify Account\n- Go to https://apify.com/\n\n### Step 2: Generate Apify Access Token\n- Go to https://console.apify.com/settings/integrations\n- Generate Token\n- Grant necessary permissions\n- Insert it into the Apify node in your n8n workflow\n\n---\n\n## 3. Google Gemini API (AI Studio) Settings\n- Go to https://aistudio.google.com/\n- Create a Google AI Studio account \n- Create an API key for Gemini https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey\n- Insert the Gemini API key inside n8n Google nodes\n\n After the webhook is triggered in n8n, you will see the data sent by HubSpot.\n- You can now add additional nodes to **process the data** (e.g., save to database, send email, perform actions in another app).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Make the Workflow Active\n- Once you are done configuring, make sure the workflow is **set to \u201cActive.\u201d**",
        "height": 1164,
        "width": 632,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "a378f105-34df-4f82-b03d-10bfcbd3bf37",
      "name": "Sticky Note8",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
